Next Saturday, @township_rebellion make their Room 2 fabric debut ✨

The German duo are an unwavering force on the global scene. Known for their unique blend of compelling synths and changeable melodies, they're also firm favourites on techno legend Oliver Koletzki’s label Stil Vor Talent. It’s a real treat to welcome them into the fabric fold for the first time. 

✨ Also joining us on 15th April will be the mighty @kollektiv_turmstrasse, who returns to Room 1 after 12+ months. Plus fabric podcast guests @marvinandguy, MIURA and @justkelly_music. Meanwhile, Tel Aviv’s @talfussman and @iamdjmoritz join the pair in Room 2. 

🎟 Advance tickets via RA.

Township Rebellion were one of the first releases on Filth on Acid with their legendary Brothers EP in 2017. Now Township Rebellion bring all their experiences together and add one to our Stamp Collection Vol 3: 'Placebo' not only surprises with dark melodies, but also with powerful synth hooklines. Make sure you play it loud! This is Filth on Acid NOW!

Remember when we played at Burning Man for the first time and found out later that @rufusdusol was among the crowd and liked it, wrote us afterwards and we joined their label? Our EP '2020' on Rose Avenue back then just opened so many doors for us with their support. Looking back we are extremly grateful for the last 3 great years. Today we are part of Rose Avenues Compilation Vol 1, joining a great group of incredible Artists. Together with Victor Pilava & Roemisch we made our very own interpretation of a classic masterpiece called "Fantasia on a Theme". Listen up and let us know how you feel! 🎻🎹🎶🔥
